snippet.textDisplay:
GUYS. BOUNTY. Listen up!

I'm from Britain, and we used paper towels for years, like many countries. But I remember around the early 2000's that Bounty came out. It had the motto of "The strongest soaker upper!" along with a really fucking catchy jingle. It was amazing. It REALLY was. Like it soaked up a lot more than normal and held it's structure so that you could use it like a J-cloth or similar textile wipe.

A few years ago they renamed it to 'Plenty' and the British went mad, there was even a small campaign to get it to be renamed to 'Bounty' but i think it lost because we have a chocolate bar with the same name.


Long story short, I understand YouTube sponsorships but I'm not a fan of these company adverts, however Bounty really is amazing and I challenge anyone to find a better company!

snippet.textDisplay:
With me I add parmesan, havarti, swiss, apple wood smoked cheddar, monterey jack, and american.

I make sure to make it creamier by substituting milk for half & half and lightly melt the butter on a low heat before adding in the h&h.

Spice-wise I tend to use a rock salt and some powdered ginger, nothing much else as I do not want to take away from the natural cheese & smoke flavours.

As I have trouble with all that dairy, I add some kind of meat like cubed pork roast or ground turkey alongside lots of freshly chopped spinach.
snippet.textOriginal:
With me I add parmesan, havarti, swiss, apple wood smoked cheddar, monterey jack, and american.

Spice-wise I tend to use a rock salt and some powdered ginger, nothing much else as I do not want to take away from the natural cheese & smoke flavours.

As I have trouble with all that dairy, I add some kind of meat like cubed pork roast or ground turkey alongside lots of freshly chopped spinach.
